snippet.textDisplay: The only time I’ll truly believe Sony has our 100% best interest at heart is getting rid of PS Now, imo they should find a way to make all PlayStation games in its history purchasable on the PlayStation store. I still love the PlayStation and am a loyal fan but that’s the one bit that doesn’t sit quite well with me, I know the reason for there being no reverse compatibility with the PS3 and the PS4, however it’s 2020, and if you ask me I’d wait another year or 2 for the PS5 to release if it meant it being reverse compatible with PS4 and PS3 and also remastering older gen games. But as the reverse comparability(disc wise) may be too much to ask, at least remaster all the games and make the purchasable on the cloud. Again I’m not an idiot who wants things and think it’s “that easy”, but tbh it’s not that hard for a company like Sony. If you guys just made more of your extensive library of games available you would legit be the greatest gaming company of all time for years to come already, literally what’s stopping you guys from actually being cemented the goat is your slight stingyness concerning PS Now and tbh also PS Plus as there can be and is a justified reason as to why it actually isn’t too bad of a thing, however I don’t agree with PS Now. I love Sony but they are not 100% for the gamers yet, but hey tbh they are pretty damn close to getting there
